### Afterlife and reincarnation
- Does not have a traditional afterlife
	- But there is a temporary one where someone is [[Unsorted/Afterlives#Rewarding/punishing Afterlife\|Rewarded/punished]]
- Instead they have [[Unsorted/Reincarnation#Samsara\|Reincarnation#Samsara]]
	- Endless cycle of births, lives, deaths, rebirths
	- Known as Samsara
- Inbetween

> [!Question]+
> How MANY souls are there?
		- Doesn't seem like a one-soul-going-between everyone sort of thing



### Caste system
- Prevents most social mobility
	- Untouchables believed to have earned their place
		- From the perspective of classism, this is awful
		- ENCOURAGES mistreatment
	- People from other regions and traditions don't fit easily into the caste system
		- Often associated with wealth/occupation/status

- Castes
	- Brahmin
	- Untouchables

- Karma

### Naraka
- A [[Class - Roots of Hell/Punishing afterlife\|Punishing afterlife]]
	- "South of the universe"
	- Name comes from the sanskrit word
- Versions
	- Bottomless pit where the most wicked people are thrown
		- Will not be reincarnated
	- Hostile jungle
	- Sypbolic retribution
		- Varies depending on the wrongdoings somebody has done
		- At least 4 sub-regions, but most have 28
- Ruled by [[Class - Roots of Hell/Ruler of Hell\|Yama]] 
	- The lord of death and justice
- [[Unsorted/Afterlives\|Sorting]]
	- Begins with a sorting scene
	- Judged by Chitragupta
		- The record keeper, comparable to other ancient religious figures
	- Once judged, get dragged to chosen hell by the [[Demons\|Yamadutas]]
- The 28 hells
	- Those who cooked animals and birds

			- The monsters are the people they wronged
	- Kalasutra: For Brahmin murderers

		- Punishment
			- Area made entirely of copper
			- Heated by fire and the sun
			- Condinually burned by every surface

			- Impossible to rest
	- Taptasurmi
		- Illicit sex, potentially with forbidden caste
		- Thrased with whips
		- Forced to embrace red hot statues of their partners
	- Vairarni
		- Those from higher castes who neglect their duties or destroy towns
			- ...or beehives
		- Endless river of feces and push full of monsters
	- Those who are selfish, with food/guests
		- Those who hate theri fathers, brahmins, or th egods
		- Worm-filled lake, where the person is eaten for 100,000 years
			- Then they turn into a worm themselves
	- Upper caste members who hunted and killed animals
		- Are used for archery practice
	- Poisoners, arsonists, mass murderers, and powerful people who abuse power for money
		- 720 vicious dogs used against the wrongdoers
	- Those who eat before acknowledging the gods, ancestors or guests
		- ...or upper caste men who force their wives to drink their semen

	- Those who lie, especially in business
